# create git ignore file
# add all the files and folders to be ignored
Dependencies - Ignores all node_modules folders in the project
This will cover the root, /backend, and /frontend folders
node_modules/

Environment Variables - Protects your secret keys and credentials
This will ignore the .env file inside your /backend directory
.env
*.env

Logs - Ignores log files that can become large and are not needed in git
.log
npm-debug.log
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

Production / Build Output - Ignores compiled or bundled files
/build
/dist
.next/
.out/

OS / Editor Specific - Ignores files generated by your operating system or code editor
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.suo
*.sln